               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 121ra-128vb; 1ra-5ra),
                     incomplete
 II) Anaphoras (fols. 5ra-118vb)
 II-1) Anaphora of the
                     Apostles (fols. 5ra-18va)
 II-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols.
                     19va-23va), preceded by an excerpt from (fols. 18va-19va)
 II-3) Anaphora
                     of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 23va-36rb)
 II-4) Anaphora of
                     St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols. 36rb-38va)
 II-5) Anaphora of St
                     Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols. 38va-48va)
 II-6) Anaphora of St John
                     Chrysostom (fols. 48va-57va)
 II-7) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols.
                     57va-68vb)
 II-8) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder (fols.
                     68vb-84rb)
 II-9) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox fathers of Nicaea (fols.
                     84rb-96ra)
 II-10) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols.
                     96ra-111ra)
 II-11) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St
                     Gregory”) (fols. 111ra-118vb).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Text I is incomplete, the beginning is missing.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
