                        <condition key="deficient">The first three quires of the Ms. are lost. Quire
                           XVI is misplaced, its proper place is before quire I, as indicated by the
                           Ethiopic quire numbers. Most of the leaves are heavily stained with dirt
                           or damaged by humidity, this sometimes renders the text poorly legible.
                           The original sewing is probably lost, the original threads are replaced
                           with narrow strips of leather. <locus target="#38">38</locus> is torn at
                           the lower inner edge, with loss of text. <locus target="#69">69</locus>,
                           74, 75, 98, 125 have been torn and mended with stitches.</condition>
